MiHaJong - Japanese Mahjong with a lot of local rules implemented
Copyright (c) 2008-2013 MihailJP, Part of rights reserved

Run on Windows XP/Vista/7 with Direct X 9+

Compiler:
- Visual C++ 2010 Express Edition (tested)
- GNU C++ 4.7 MinGW/MSYS (NOT tested)

Build-time requirements:
- Ruby interpreter with ruby-lzma gem
- [Alternative] Python2/3 with LZMA support (needed if ruby-lzma unavailable)

Dependencies:
- liblua (v5.1 or later, http://www.lua.org/download.html) [*1]
[*1] Statically linked when compiled with VC++.

Optional dependencies:
- libogg and libvorbis (http://www.xiph.org/downloads/) [*1]
- GuruGuruSMF (http://gurugurusmf.migmig.net/) [*2]
[*1] Statically linked when compiled with VC++.
[*2] Windows only.

See readme.txt for more (written in Japanese)
See playing.txt for how to play (written in Japanese)
See license.txt for license text (mainly written in Japanese)
history.txt describes each release.

** We use Japanese language in this project **
